<comment type="function">
<text evidence="1 2 3">Catalyzes the phosphatidyl group transfer from one phosphatidylglycerol molecule to another to form cardiolipin (CL) (diphosphatidylglycerol) and glycerol. Can also catalyze phosphatidyl group transfer to water to form phosphatidate.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="catalytic activity">
<reaction evidence="1 2">
<text>2 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) = a cardiolipin + glycerol</text>
